    <item>
      <title>About Yagnya</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/wiaposts/about-yagnya/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 20 Jul 2016 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/wiaposts/about-yagnya/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;../../assets/images/wiapost/5023-About-Yagnya.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;About Yagnya&#34; /&gt;
      
    &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;About Yagnya 
    &lt;div id=&#34;about-yagnya&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#about-yagnya&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A process that has five elements.  &lt;br&gt;
A goal, A sponsor (Yajmaan), A Performer (Purohit),  &lt;br&gt;
A Deity (Devta) and Material (Havan Material) involved.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yagnya is not the Sacrifice of an animal  &lt;br&gt;
Yagnya is not Sacrifice of even of a flower  &lt;br&gt;
English word Sacrifice closely resembles the samskrut word Bali.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A Yagnya is Satvik when the goal of Yajmaan is a public welfare  &lt;br&gt;
A Yagnya is Rajsik when the goal of Yajmaan is self-glory,  &lt;br&gt;
name, fame, and receiving wealth from the Yagya Devta for himself.  &lt;br&gt;
A Yagnya is Tamasik when Yajmaan has not defined the goal or  &lt;br&gt;
the process is not followed or dues are not given to rightful people  &lt;br&gt;
and all which creates problems for everybody around.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
